## Meta Tags & Document Head Management

### Always use react-helmet-async for meta tag management
```typescript
import { Helmet } from 'react-helmet-async';

// Wrap root with HelmetProvider
import { HelmetProvider } from 'react-helmet-async';
```

### Required meta tags for every page
- Title (50-60 characters)
- Description (150-160 characters)
- Open Graph tags (og:title, og:description, og:image, og:url, og:type)
- Twitter Card tags
- Canonical URL
- Viewport meta tag
- Charset meta tag

### Example implementation
```typescript
<Helmet>
  <title>Page Title | Site Name</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Page description" />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://example.com/page" />
  <meta property="og:title" content="Page Title" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="Page description" />
  <meta property="og:image" content="https://example.com/image.jpg" />
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://example.com/page" />
  <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
  <meta name="twitter:title" content="Page Title" />
  <meta name="twitter:description" content="Page description" />
</Helmet>
```

## Routing & URLs

### Use React Router v6+ for client-side routing
- Always define clear, semantic URL structures
- Use lowercase URLs with hyphens (kebab-case)
- Avoid query parameters for main content pages

### URL best practices
```typescript
// Good
/blog/react-seo-best-practices
/products/laptop-accessories

// Avoid
/blog?id=123
/products/LaptopAccessories
```

## Performance Optimization

### Code splitting and lazy loading
```typescript
import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';

const BlogPost = lazy(() => import('./pages/BlogPost'));

<Suspense fallback={<LoadingSpinner />}>
  <BlogPost />
</Suspense>
```

### Image optimization
- Use WebP format with fallbacks
- Implement lazy loading with loading="lazy"
- Always specify width and height attributes
- Use srcset for responsive images
- Compress images before deployment

```typescript
<img
  src="/images/hero.webp"
  alt="Descriptive alt text"
  width="1200"
  height="630"
  loading="lazy"
  srcSet="/images/hero-small.webp 400w, /images/hero-medium.webp 800w, /images/hero-large.webp 1200w"
/>
```

## Semantic HTML

### Use proper heading hierarchy
- One h1 per page (main page title)
- Follow sequential order (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Never skip heading levels

### Use semantic HTML5 elements
```typescript
<header>
<nav>
<main>
<article>
<section>
<aside>
<footer>
```

### Avoid div soup
```typescript
// Bad
<div className="article">
  <div className="header">...</div>
</div>

// Good
<article>
  <header>...</header>
</article>
```

## Accessibility (Impacts SEO)

### ARIA labels and roles
- Add aria-label for icons and buttons without text
- Use proper role attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation works

### Focus management
- Manage focus on route changes
- Visible focus indicators
- Skip to main content link

```typescript
<button aria-label="Close menu" onClick={closeMenu}>
  <CloseIcon />
</button>

<a href="#main-content" className="skip-link">
  Skip to main content
</a>
```

